OL,4,Cowner under fire after new disability
OL,5,Cpass
OL,7,FThe parent company of some of London's
OL,8,Fbiggest attractions is under fire
OL,9,Fafter claims it no longer supports
OL,10,Fpeople with hidden disabilities by no
OL,11,Flonger offering a queue pass.
OL,13,FMerlin Entertainments owns sites such
OL,14,Fas the Legoland parks, Madame
OL,15,FTaussauds, and Chessington World of
OL,16,FAdventures. It also operates major UK
OL,17,Ftheme parks like Alton Towers and
OL,18,FThorpe Park.
